reviews.review_comment:
Hmm, to be honest, there were too many items out of stock! 
                    The taste was average. The sashimi was delicious, but the yakitori was disappointing. 
                    The drinks had a cheap flavor. 
                    While the course seemed to offer good value, ordering a la carte turned out to be quite expensive. 
                    I wonder if the taste and ingredients vary by day, but overall, I was left feeling disappointed.

I had made a reservation for a 2-hour all-you-can-drink course with squid included (JPY 6,000). 
                    
                    I had heard that there might be no squid available depending on the weather, so I was glad to find out that they had a fresh supply on the day of my reservation! 
                    
                    It was a Thursday, and due to the busy season in December, the taxi was late, so I arrived 30 minutes late to the gathering. 
                    
                    Even though I was only 30 minutes late, everyone had already finished the final dish of the hot pot—champon noodles. 
                    
                    They joked, "You probably wouldn’t eat much anyway." 
                    
                    I wish they had saved me a little food to enjoy. 
                    
                    All the staff were cheerful and friendly. 
                    
                    It was a great meal!

The fresh sashimi of squid is, of course, amazing, but the simmered fish is absolutely delicious! The staff were very attentive, and the atmosphere was pleasant as well.
                    
                    The seafood is fantastic, but there are also plenty of meat options at reasonable prices (｡•ᴗ•｡). I don't often visit Saga, but after trying the simmered fish this time, I definitely want to come back to Saga again ⸜(*ˊᗜˋ*)⸝.
                    
                    It was a delightful experience! (人 -᷄ ᴗ -᷅ ｡)

I visited on a weekday evening.
                    I was lucky to secure a reservation without any issues, even though I booked around that evening.
                    
                    The seafood, including the squid from Yanbo, was indeed delicious, as expected from its reputation.
                    The squid was still alive just before being prepared, and I could see the brown spots near its head moving.

I mistakenly ordered the "Uni-Ku" beef sushi thinking it was made with Saga beef and sea urchin. 
                    There were plenty of choices for Japanese sake✨. 
                    The local sake was delicious, but tonight I treated myself to Dassai, making for a fantastic meal along with great drinks.
I received a complimentary birthday dessert cake from the restaurant's kindness.✨

reviews.review_title: Highly recommended for visitors from outside the prefecture
reviews.review_comment:
Delicious fish awaits you here! ⭐︎
                    We had a great time celebrating with friends.
                    We reserved the 5000 JPY all-you-can-drink course featuring live squid sashimi.
                    At first, I was worried that 5000 JPY for an all-you-can-drink course with live squid sashimi seemed too good to be true. Would the other dishes be disappointing? Would we miss out on other services? But once the course began, a wonderful array of dishes including salad, sashimi, fried items, and simmered dishes kept coming, and we were all completely full.
                    
                    Unfortunately, there was no squid that day, so we couldn't have the live sashimi, but the manager kindly upgraded our sashimi selection since it was a celebration, which delighted everyone. Our group tends to be picky about sashimi, but everyone unanimously agreed it was delicious.
                    
                    Though we were a bit cheeky in taking full advantage of the discounts for group size, dessert plates, and even the rental of ceremonial sashes, the manager and other staff were incredibly courteous and made our time enjoyable.
                    
                    I was so excited that I forgot to take pictures of the food, but I plan to have the live sashimi next time and will definitely share photos then.
It was the best 'Kazunoko Hirame'.

The squid was fresh and delicious! 
                    Additionally, the staff warmly welcomed us and saw us off.
You can easily enjoy dishes like squid here. The owner and staff are very friendly, which creates a calming atmosphere!

The service is excellent, and the food is incredibly delicious. 
                    The beer is served ice-cold. 
                    I definitely want to come back again.

I had incredibly fresh and delicious dishes.
                    I definitely want to visit again.
Just a regular izakaya.
The sashimi was fresh and delicious.

I mistakenly ordered the "Uni-Ku" beef sushi thinking it was made with Saga beef and sea urchin. 
                    There were plenty of choices for Japanese sake✨. 
                    The local sake was delicious, but tonight I treated myself to Dassai, making for a fantastic meal along with great drinks.
I received a complimentary birthday dessert cake from the restaurant's kindness.✨

Everything is delicious here!
                    My recommendation is the fried burdock root. It's well-seasoned and very satisfying!
                    It's a world of difference compared to the typical frozen ones. 
                    The kids really enjoyed the yakitori rice bowl, happily devouring it. 
                    When I ordered the mildly spicy dan dan noodles, it ended up tasting like shoyu ramen.
                    The menu has a great variety, and I definitely want to come back!

I am completely full.
                    It was delicious.

The owner and the staff were very kind, and I had a wonderful time.
                    The dishes were delicious and offered great value for the price.

The dishes were plentiful and delicious! 
                    They even grill the items for those who arrive late. 
                    Such thoughtful service—what a great restaurant!
The horse sashimi was delicious.
Everything was delicious.

Chic and nice, 
                    located on a quiet street.

reviews.review_title: Yaki Bito - Delicious Yakitori, but the Chinese dishes are also GREAT!
reviews.review_comment:
Located about a 5-minute walk from Tosu Station, this stylish yakitori restaurant has a spotless interior. 
                    There’s no smoke that you often find in yakitori places, and the young staff members have a great vibe.
                    
                    The main yakitori dishes are crafted with care and are delicious. 
                    The pork belly, which is a must-try, is large and satisfying—just perfect!
                    
                    What sets this place apart from other yakitori restaurants is the availability of authentic Chinese cuisine. 
                    We ordered gyoza and Sichuan-style mapo tofu. Both exceeded typical izakaya standards.
                    The beer went down smoothly (unfortunately, I couldn’t take pictures at the counter).
                    
                    They also offer a variety of other dishes, including sashimi and rice options to finish off your meal,
                    making it a great spot that caters to any situation.
